---
// Privacy Policy Page
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy Policy for DriveSchoolPro. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when using our driving school management platform.">
  <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
  <div class="bg-gray-100 py-3">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'Privacy Policy' }
      ]} />
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: 23 March 2026</p>
        <div class="prose max-w-none">

<h2>1. Who We Are</h2>

<p>DriveSchoolPro is operated by <strong>LEAVE.REVIEW LTD</strong> (Company No. 05408918), a company registered in England and Wales with its registered office at 124 City Road, London, England, EC1V 2NX.</p>

<p>For the purposes of UK data protection legislation, LEAVE.REVIEW LTD is the <strong>data controller</strong> for the personal data described in this policy.</p>

<p>If you have any questions about this policy or how we handle your data, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@driveschoolpro.com">privacy@driveschoolpro.com</a>.</p>

<h2>2. What Data We Collect</h2>

<p>We collect the following categories of personal data:</p>

<h3>Account information</h3>
<p>When you register for DriveSchoolPro, we collect your name, email address, phone number, and business details (such as your driving school name and address).</p>

<h3>Student records</h3>
<p>Driving instructors and school administrators use DriveSchoolPro to manage student data, which may include a student's name, date of birth, driving licence details, learning progress notes, and lesson history. This data is entered by the account holder and is their responsibility to obtain appropriate consent for.</p>

<h3>Payment information</h3>
<p>Payments are processed securely by <strong>Stripe</strong>. We never store your full card number, CVV, or other sensitive payment credentials. Stripe provides us with a tokenised reference and basic transaction details (amount, date, last four digits of card).</p>

<h3>Usage data</h3>
<p>We automatically collect information about how you use the platform, including pages visited, features used, session duration, browser type, device type, and IP address. This helps us understand how the service is used and where improvements can be made.</p>

<h3>Cookies and similar technologies</h3>
<p>We use cookies and local storage to manage your session, remember your preferences, and (with your consent) analyse how visitors use our website. See Section 8 for full details.</p>

<h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>

<p>We use personal data for the following purposes:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Providing and improving the service</strong> — to deliver the DriveSchoolPro platform, maintain your account, and develop new features</li>
<li><strong>Processing payments</strong> — to handle subscription billing and invoicing via Stripe</li>
<li><strong>Transactional communications</strong> — to send lesson reminders, receipts, account notifications, and important service updates</li>
<li><strong>Analysing usage</strong> — to understand how the platform is used so we can improve it (analytics only loaded with your consent)</li>
<li><strong>Legal and regulatory obligations</strong> — to meet our obligations under HMRC, DVSA record-keeping requirements, and other applicable law</li>
</ul>

<p>We do not use your data for advertising or sell it to third parties.</p>

<h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>

<p>Under UK GDPR Article 6, we rely on the following legal bases:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Contract (Art. 6(1)(b))</strong> — processing your account information and student records is necessary to provide the service you have signed up for</li>
<li><strong>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f))</strong> — analysing usage patterns to improve the platform, fraud prevention, and security monitoring, where these do not override your rights</li>
<li><strong>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c))</strong> — retaining financial records for HMRC requirements and other regulatory compliance</li>
<li><strong>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a))</strong> — loading analytics cookies and sending optional marketing communications, where you have explicitly agreed</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>

<p>We share personal data only with the following third-party service providers, who process data on our behalf under appropriate data processing agreements:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing (see <a href="https://stripe.com/gb/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Stripe's Privacy Policy</a>)</li>
<li><strong>Neon</strong> — cloud database hosting (data stored encrypted at rest)</li>
<li><strong>Vercel</strong> — website hosting and content delivery</li>
<li><strong>Resend</strong> — transactional email delivery (lesson reminders, receipts, notifications)</li>
</ul>

<p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or trade personal data with any third party for their own marketing purposes.</p>

<h2>6. Data Retention</h2>

<p>We retain personal data for the following periods:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Active account data</strong> — retained for as long as your account is active</li>
<li><strong>Financial records</strong> — retained for 6 years following the end of the relevant tax year, as required by HMRC</li>
<li><strong>Deleted accounts</strong> — personal data is anonymised within 30 days of account deletion; financial records are retained for the period above to meet legal obligations</li>
<li><strong>Usage analytics</strong> — aggregated and anonymised after 26 months</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Your Rights</h2>

<p>Under UK GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Right of access (Art. 15)</strong> — you can request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
<li><strong>Right to rectification (Art. 16)</strong> — you can ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
<li><strong>Right to erasure (Art. 17)</strong> — you can request that we delete your personal data ("right to be forgotten"), subject to legal retention obligations</li>
<li><strong>Right to restrict processing (Art. 18)</strong> — you can ask us to pause processing your data in certain circumstances</li>
<li><strong>Right to data portability (Art. 20)</strong> — you can request your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
<li><strong>Right to object (Art. 21)</strong> — you can object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
<li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> — where processing is based on consent, you can withdraw it at any time without affecting the lawfulness of prior processing</li>
</ul>

<p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@driveschoolpro.com">privacy@driveschoolpro.com</a>. We will respond within one calendar month.</p>

<p>You also have the right to <strong>lodge a complaint</strong> with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a> or by calling 0303 123 1113.</p>

<h2>8. Cookies</h2>

<p>We use two categories of cookies:</p>

<h3>Essential cookies</h3>
<p>These are always active and are necessary for the website and application to function correctly. They handle session management, authentication, and security. They do not track you across other websites and cannot be disabled.</p>

<h3>Analytics cookies</h3>
<p>We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our website — for example, which pages are visited most often and where visitors come from. These cookies are only loaded if you click <strong>Accept All</strong> on the cookie consent banner. No analytics cookies are set if you choose <strong>Necessary Only</strong>.</p>

<p>We do not use advertising cookies or cross-site tracking cookies of any kind.</p>

<h3>Changing your cookie preferences</h3>
<p>You can change your cookie preferences at any time by clicking the button below to re-open the consent banner:</p>

<p>
  <button
    onclick="window.cookieConsent && window.cookieConsent.revoke()"
    class="text-sm px-4 py-2 rounded-lg border border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors cursor-pointer"
  >
    Manage cookie preferences
  </button>
</p>

<p>You can also install the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a> to prevent Google Analytics from collecting data about your visits across any website.</p>

<h2>9. Data Security</h2>

<p>We take the security of your data seriously and use the following measures to protect it:</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Encryption in transit</strong> — all data between your browser and our servers is encrypted using HTTPS/TLS</li>
<li><strong>Encryption at rest</strong> — data stored in our database is encrypted at rest</li>
<li><strong>Multi-tenant data isolation</strong> — your organisation's data is logically separated from other accounts; no other DriveSchoolPro user can access your data</li>
<li><strong>PCI DSS compliant payment processing</strong> — all card payments are handled by Stripe, which is certified to PCI DSS Level 1</li>
<li><strong>Access controls</strong> — access to production systems is restricted to authorised personnel only, and reviewed regularly</li>
</ul>

<p>No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure. If you believe your data has been compromised, please contact us immediately at <a href="mailto:privacy@driveschoolpro.com">privacy@driveschoolpro.com</a>.</p>

<h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>

<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in the law, our services, or our data practices. When we make material changes, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.</p>

<p>We encourage you to review this page periodically. Continued use of DriveSchoolPro after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

<h2>11. Contact Us</h2>

<p>For any data protection queries, to exercise your rights, or to raise a concern:</p>

<p>
  <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@driveschoolpro.com">privacy@driveschoolpro.com</a><br />
  <strong>Data Controller:</strong> LEAVE.REVIEW LTD<br />
  <strong>Registered address:</strong> 124 City Road, London, England, EC1V 2NX<br />
  <strong>Company number:</strong> 05408918
</p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
